\begin_layout Standard
Every non-trivial text describes interactions and relations between people,
 institutions, activities, events and so on.
 What we know about the world consists in large part of such relations,
 and that knowledge contributes to the understanding of what texts refer
 to.
 Newly found relations can in turn become part of this knowledge that is
 stored for future use.
